NixOS is high-level declarative, so you&#x27;re reading high-level config diffs when the AI agent is pitching changes.<p>Unless you&#x27;re brand new to Linux or computing, it&#x27;s not a mystery what a given nix config change is ever doing.<p>You can probably guess what this does:<p><pre><code>    networking.firewall.allowedTCPPorts = [ 8080, 9000 ];
</code></pre>
The things to know about the OS are high level things. The rest of its idiosyncrasies you learn just in time through daily exposure like anything else.

